== Attitudes of EU Party Groups  ==

 * EU Verts/ALE (Greens/EFA): 100% helpful on all information infrastructure dossiers
 * EU GUE/NGL/LEFT (post-communists): 100% helpful, similar to Greens
 * EU [http://www.europarl.eu.int/edd/ EDD]: 100% helpful on all information infrastructure dossiers, very critical of EU laws in general
 * EU [http://www.europarl.eu.int/uen/ UEN]: 100% helpful on swpat dossier, less so on IPRED
 * EU NI (non-aligned): voted for clear limitation of patentability
 * EU ELDR (Liberals): 50% helpful (UK and Manders (NL, JURI) unhelpful, Boogerd (NL D66), Sterckx (BE VLD) and Olle Schmidt (SE) helpful), under pressure from [:SwpatbolkesteinEn: Bolkestein] (NL/VVD)
 * EU PSE (Socialists / Social Democrats): 50% helpful (FR and BE very helpful; UK and SE very unhelpful, DE ambiguous), under pressure from "their" rapporteur [:SwpatamccarthyEn: McCarthy], whom they managed to nearly neutralise in summer 2003 
 * EU EPP-DE (Conservatives + Christdems): 20% helpful (e.g. [:ElectAtPart0405De: AT], FI), 80% blindly follow their "IP experts" (= patent lobby soldiers) [:SwpatjwuermelingEn: Wuermeling] (DE), [:SwpatmharbourEn: Harbour] (UK) and [:SwpatjfourtouEn: Fourtou] (FR)

